                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The United Nations Security Council held its 488th Meeting on August 17 at 3 p.
                    m.; for the record, see U.N. document S/PV.488. The debate on Korea continued,
                    but no action was taken to break the procedural deadlock which prevented voting
                    on any substantive proposals.</p>
                <p>Ambassador Austin made a statement setting forth the three great objectives to
                    which the United Nations was committed in Korea: to end the breach of the peace;
                    to provide a demonstration of United Nations achievement which would deter any
                    future aggression; and to aid the establishment by the Korean people of a free,
                    unified, and independent nation.</p>
            </div>
